Options.OPTION_DESCRIPTION[Carto.Carto.M: The file format of the exported files.
The naming convention for the exported files.

Enter the custom file naming conventions. Some available tokens to display the attributes: {City} = the name of the city, {Map} = the name of the map, {Feature} = the feature type. **Caution**: if multiple files are exported under the same name, only the last one will be saved.
The WGS84 latitude (decimal degree) of the map center. The input should be in the range between -90 to 90, where minus numbers indicate the southern hemisphere.
The WGS84 longitude (decimal degree) of the map center. The input should be in the range between -180 to 180, where minus numbers indicate western hemisphere.
Open the exported files' directory.
Export game objects into geospatial files.
The current running Carto version.
Open the user manual on GitHub (<https://github.com/taipei-native/Carto/wiki>).
Reset all Carto's settings.
Are you sure you want to reset mod settings?
Options.OPTION_DESCRIPTION[Carto.Carto.M: **(Vector)** Export area features, including districts and map tiles.
**(Vector)** Export building features, including spawnables and placeables.
**(Vector)** Export network features, including roads and tracks.
**(Raster)** Export the grayscale map of the terrain.
**(Raster)** Export the grayscale map of the water bodies.
**(Vector)** Export zoning cells.
Select the feature type you want to configure. (Due to a known issue, some fields will not appear until you double click the "Show / Hide Advanced" button to reload the UI.)
The special code given to buildings for identification purposes.
The extent of the surface region.
The title of the in-game objects.
The title of the in-game virtual chain enterprises.
The sub-division of the in-game objects.
The in-game coordinates of the region's centroid.
The line followed the center of linear objects.
The in-game UI color of the zoning type.
The number of companies.
The development intensity of the zoning type.
The distance from the surface to the bottom.
The way vehicles driving along to, relative to the network.
The outside limit of the surface region.
The height above the in-game origin.
The number of workers.
The style of the network, such as viaducts or tunnels.
The distance above the in-game origin.
The number of families.
The measurement of the extent of the strip-like objects from end to end.
The measurement of in-game building's upgrade progress.
Carto's classification of the in-game objects.
The merchandise sold by stores or factories.
The number of dwellers.
The style of the assets.
The purchase status of the map tiles.
The measurement of the extent of the strip-like objects from side to side.
The water depth of the worldmap, which includes the area outside of the playable region.
The elevation of the worldmap, which includes the area outside of the playable region.
The classification of designated development purposes, which can be residential, commercial, industrial, office or a mixture of them.

Select the format of the exported GeoTIFFs. **Int16** is the default option, which provides a reasonable ratio between the details and the file size. **Float32** includes extra information in decimals, but the file size is twice as big. **Norm16** normalizes Int16's data and can be re-imported to the asset editor.
When enabled, homeless residents and households will be counted.
When enabled, unzoned (empty) zoning cells will be exported. Disable this option to reduce exported file size.
When enabled, the color fields exported along with the zonings are replaced by Zone Color Changer's colors.
Enable all fields so that they are exported.
Are you sure you want to enable all fields?
Carto.export.ERROR[Latitude]: The inputted "Latitude" value is invalid. Please make sure the value is a number between -90 and 90.
Carto.export.ERROR[Longitude]: The inputted "Longitude" value is invalid. Please make sure the value is a number between -180 and 180.
Carto.export.ERROR[ShareViolation]: One or more files can not be accessed due to sharing violation; Please close the programs (e.g., QGIS and ArcGIS) that open the file right now. These files are: {FILES}
Carto.export.ERROR[MissingSpatialFields]: One or more selected features do not have any selected spatial fields; Due to a known issue, some fields will not appear until you double click the "Show / Hide Advanced" button to reload the UI. These features are: {FEATURES}
